summary: This appears to be a Bank of America legal order processing document, likely a response to a subpoena or court order from the United States Attorney's Office, requesting customer and account profile information. The document is part of case number 2019R01059 and contains multiple redacted account entries.
keyFacts: Bank of America was served with a legal order from the United States Attorney's Office in case 2019R01059.
The document is an attachment to an affidavit of a Bank of America bank officer/custodian of records.
The document contains multiple customer and account profile entries, but all identifying information (account numbers, names, addresses, phone numbers, emails) is redacted.
The reference number D082319000153 suggests the order was processed around August 23, 2019.
This document demonstrates law enforcement's use of financial subpoenas to investigate the Epstein case.
